<br>
(2) It's their game and they can do what they want but if they were smart they would have been taking notes from all the popular boards over the years.  Some messages sing loud and true over and over again.  I won't get into all of them, but shame on them for not listening.<br>
<br>
(3) Roleplay is awesome if the game is really developed around it.  Rather, I find that many times I'm playing a fantasy MM FPS.  Develop the history properly and really add dynamic content (like the frog attack--although I hated that that's a good sign).  Don't keep the world static and don't charge us for those kind of changes!<br>
<br>
(4) Questing is awesome when: (A) There is real story-line and the game's history is strong. Otherwise it sucks, which is how I find many of the quests in EQ--thus I don't quest. (B) The quest isn't so damn tedious (i.e. not so many rare drops of off rare mobs). Otherwise refer to what happens in 'A' above.<br>
<br>
(5) Item decay to quell mudflation is just wrong.  It's a damn game!  Who the hell cares what Joe Schmoe has and more importantly why on God's green earth would the item just decay to nothingness.  Damn I've used my non-uber chef knives for years and they work just fine and don't show any sign of just disintegrating.  If you care that item 'X' has 'Y' assigned value so much become a damn accountant and get out of my game.<br>
<br>
Lastly, OT, I could never understand when some mob was beating the piss out of me or my guild and he was clearly holding some item in his hand that when we killed him he didn't drop that item.  Or why is it that named mobs who would obviously have some story line behind them wouldn't ALWAYS carry their items of &quot;ass kickedness&quot;.  Explain any reasonable reason for these in a fantasy role playing game.  I can't.<br>
<br>
