<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215660" target="top">Look Under My Robe!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zurrenal>Zurren AL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 606<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 5:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Keep in mind I'm not rah-rah EQ2, and have no intent on buying it. However, I will play a bit of a devils advocate.<br>
<br>
Most of peoples complaints about tradeskills, item wear, item loss, etc, all seem to be comming from a very EQ1-centric point of view.<br>
<br>
Yeah, if SoE was to implement item wear/loss/etc into EQ, it would blow goats more then I'd care to imagine. Yeh, I've had items I've used for 3 years on my toon and never gotten around to upgrading till rescently (kkthnxdustybloodstainedgloves). Why would it suck hard in EQ? because the game was not designed around these concepts.<br>
<br>
In EQ2, if the game is being designed and based on the concepts of item loss, decay and tradeskills, most likely (or one can hope) that the rate of item flow in/out of the game and how people obtain items is done in a natural manner which does not involve exessive backfeeding.<br>
<br>
Stop thinking of EQ2 concepts in EQ1 terms, cause well, in that case yeah, it is pretty shitty.<br>
